    watcher.watch("/path/to/watch", RecursiveMode::Recursive)?;

    // Keep the watcher alive
    loop {
        std::thread::sleep(Duration::from_secs(1));
    }
}
```

### Key Configuration Options

- **`with_poll_interval()`** - Sets how frequently the poller checks for changes
- **`with_compare_contents()`** - Enables content comparison for detecting changes
- Default poll interval is typically around 30 seconds

### Dependencies (Cargo.toml)

```toml
[dependencies]
notify = "6.1"  # or latest version
```

### When to Use PollWatcher

- On systems where native file system notifications aren't available
- When you need more control over polling behavior
- For network-mounted file systems that don't support inotify/FSEvents

